    Truly amazing Riad. The location is a little hidden which is actually very welcome. The room is well decorated and has to be the best nights sleep we have had this trip, deffiently didn't want to get up in the mornings. The main 'court 
    Truly amazing Riad. The location is a little hidden which is actually very welcome. The room is well decorated and has to be the best nights sleep we have had this trip, deffiently didn't want to get up in the mornings. The main 'court yard' is beautiful and with 3 very special friends wondering around you should watch your step. The service we been receiving here is second to none! The staff are all friendly and willing to help in any way, you'll be given knowledge of the go to places in the area and the sights you must go and see. They are always happy to answer any questions and on the off chance they don't know, they find someone who does. The terrace is peaceful and lovely just to lay and read in the sun with a drink by your side, even if it's just to pass a bit of time till dinner. Once you get a bit used to the surrounding streets it's easy and quick to get to many places for lunch or dinner a couple minutes walk at the most. They have even more to offer! Spa and desert day trips are available just ask they'll even give you a wake up call if you so wish. Will definitely be telling friends and family about this Riad and anyone else who's willing to listen. They don't treat you as guests whilst you are there you are family!!

    Medina

    Hammam bath houses and covered spice and textile souks line the maze of cobblestoned lanes in the Medina, which occupies Marrakeshs original fortified citadel. At night, Jemaa el-Fna square teems with snake charmers, folk dancers, and street food vendors serving all manner of food. Bahia Palace and Le Jardin Secret are 19th-century complexes open to the public, with ornate courtyards, mosaics, and gardens.
